comment: Flashed with left hand on bottom corner of volume (below only labeled start). Another climber let me know during the comp both hands were labeled. Apparently I can't start it with the comp start hand. Makes sense since it felt soft with the volume start. I either flashed or can't start﹐ Oh well. #bringtwostarthandsback

Finally was able to finish this thanks to Boris A's beta. I'm surprised by how hard the finishing beta is to figure out. This took me the longest on the set to finish. It's not physically harder than the rest﹐ but much more challenging to unlock. Frustratingly well set.
Simple but solid outdoorsy climb. Challenging at the top.

Hard﹐ delicate start﹐ but good. I luckily caught the far volume with my left fingertips to kill the barndoor on my flash attempt. Figured out the start sans-volume afterwards. Most people seem to be using the arete to start﹐ which presumably is off.

I was convinced the toehook wouldn't work for me with my long legs﹐ but it eventually did. I was pretty close to finishing it with without a toehook (or the high﹐ left hold)﹐ but in the end the toehook was the easier and better solution.
I found the finish moves to be the hardest on the slab wall (including 6s﹐ 7s﹐ & 8). Might just be me.
Fun like the 7 with the same start﹐ but with a gimmicky finish. Also about as hard as the 5s on the same wall once you work out beta.
Skipped the pinch with a mantle
Fun﹐ but no harder than the 5s on this wall
Committing cross in the middle. Frustrating to work out the beta but ended up liking this one.
Matching the finish hold was my crux. Scary fall
Finish was a little tricky. Enjoyed this one
Not too bad if you're taller. Started with wide hands﹐ since start holds are now ambiguous...
The label on the climb is a for a v3﹐ it's more like a v5. Most of the low grades in this corner are sandbagged for some reason. Good climb though.
Challenging beginning! A first glance this looks like it should be pretty easy considering the huge jugs﹐ but ends to with some surprisingly powerful moves. Good climb.
Either I sent this with an unlabeled finish hold or there wasn't one.. ?‍♂️
Another sandbagged climb in this corner.
Felt harder than the 12s on this wall.
I personally found this 5 harder than the 6s and 7s on this wall.
Cool first move; body wedge finish ftw!
The two moves at the lip (before and over) were very powerful. Super bouldery fun!
Accidently went straight up & skipped the holds out right﹐ fun move though it might add to the grade.
Felt like I almost broke my wrist on the second move on my first attempt﹐ climber beware. Cool climb minus the possibility of injury.
Matching the finish is tricky﹐ a little soft overall. Actually this recent mezzanine set is softer than normal.
Stiff opening sequence for a v3
Chimneyed my way up my second go after slipping off the finish. I'll have to try the intended beta again.
Tricky start with one hand on the volume.
Not sure if I broke the beta or unlocked it. Cool climb either way.
Pretty fun﹐ but a bit stiff for 10b (also reachy).
Felt like 11d/12a﹐ though there are definitely some harder 11s in the gym. Fun though.
A proud send. I had to work the moves on this over a few sessions. The crux for me was the first few moves through the crimps at the top. Great climb.
Soft for the grade with a couple nice rests﹐ but fun.
Heady crux sequence at the sixth (?) bolt.
That finish match went from impossible to very comfortable.
Felt harder than the black 12d on the same wall
Had to work hard on this one﹐ ended up really liking it.
The pocket finger swap was interesting
I enjoyed working the moves on this guy
As a taller climber﹐ that start was incredibly uncomfortable
Some spicy moves. Felt like 11b﹐ or maybe I just had terrible beta.
intimidating﹐ big move to the second bolt
Cool movement﹐ surprisingly terrible last hold.
Stemmed the whole problem using side wall; I think I read it wrong.
not v9﹐ should be a v7
